accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Series 4 is restricted until 2022. Series 6, 8, 9 (microfilm), 10, and 12 are restricted for 75 years from date of creation. Otherwise, the materials are open for research use. Audio-visual materials are not available in original format, and must be reformatted to a digital use copy.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: All requests to reproduce, publish, quote from, or otherwise use collection materials must be submitted in writing to the Head of Special Collections and University Archives, Stanford University Libraries, Stanford, California 94305-6064. Consent is given on behalf of Special Collections as the owner of the physical items and is not intended to include or imply permission from the copyright owner. Such permission must be obtained from the copyright owner, heir(s) or assigns. See: http://library.stanford.edu/spc/using-collections/permission-publish. Restrictions also apply to digital representations of the original materials. Use of digital files is restricted to research and educational purposes.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The records are arranged in 12 series, many of which were previously cataloged under different call numbers.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Collection was previously cataloged under four other call numbers (SCM0043, SC0043, SC0128, and SC0610). Known accessions include 1984-046 (Series 2); 1994-114 (Series 3); 1998-153 (Series 5); 2013-027 (Series 6); 1990-035 (Series 8); and 2016-113 (Series 9); 2017-067 (Series 10); Early correspondence (Series 11); and 1997-180 (Series 12).

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Collection consists of letters to the Office of the Registrar, David Starr Jordan, and Orrin Leslie Elliott; minutes of the Committee on Admissions and Advanced Standing; freshman admission ledgers; grade reports & transcripts on microfilm; and annotated publications produced by the Office of the Registrar.

scopecontent.p: Records include letters from the Committee on Recommendation of Teachers and from the Appointment Secretary, 1904-1916; the Registrar's letters, 1905-1911; and miscellaneous Registrar's Office documents, 1905-1950. Also includes correspondence 1900-1905 (primarily 1904-1905).

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The original records in this series were gleaned from a much larger mass of material received and retained by the Registrar's Office during the first four decades of the university's history. The material found in this collection represents that portion deemed most valuable as primary research material or most usefully representative of the larger body of documents. Specific examples include letters from university trustees, faculty, administrators, staff, students, and alumni regarding such matters as admission, grades, class registration, and certification of credits and degrees. General university matters and business concerns are also frequent topics in the correspondence. In addition to two boxes of incoming correspondence, 1891-1913, the collection includes copybooks of outgoing correspondence for 1900-1925, most of which is signed by the registrar. Other items in the collection are correspondence generated by the University Committee on Graduate Study (1912-1915) and by the Student Executive Committee (1900-1915), press clippings concerning Stanford (1924-1928), and memoranda and records concerning cheating, actions of the academic council, and particular scholarships.
